只單單從中描述上帝的愛來看
整個強忍著在電影院裡哭得小聲點
我想我若是自己一個人在家看一定又哭到崩潰的那種

當場景出現...Multnomah Fall馬特諾瑪瀑布
整個起雞皮疙瘩，在橋上的那幾幕
讓我想起我也曾經站在那個地方，開心的拍著照

裡面有很多觸動我的地方，
有些己經被醫治了，有些還在努力中
看著男主角一路克服的過程
真的很揪心
有好幾幕都覺得自己是電影裡的主角
那種痛真的只有上帝知道

謝謝耶穌祢讓我今天獲得你滿滿的愛

We did a hike the other day in an area that was protected by a beautiful valley near a spot I know well. I chose not to let him off leash in the literal sense of the term - but I did allow him to walk back from the trail head to the truck while dragging his long line. He stuck right by my side for the duration, and the sound of the rope slithering behind him captured his attention; he quickly pounced on it, then took himself for a walk! "Look, mom! I'm my own boss!" He says. I'm very proud of how well Ivar stuck close to me during this brief experiment, but I don't think we'll be making a habit of it anytime soon! At a different point on our hike, Ivar heard a deer run off through the trees and immediately bounded toward it, but this time, I had a firm hold on his line, and was able to prevent him from going off on a hunt!
